<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4427] Skip topicGroups with no tasks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4427</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the StreamPartitionAssignor&apos;s &quot;assign&quot; method does not handle cases where we don&apos;t have tasks for a particular topic group. E.g., code like this might give an NPE:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;for (TaskId task : tasksByTopicGroup.get(topicGroupId))&quot; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to handle the above cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
